We encourages anybody to take the 90-day challenge to see what the product can do.

Most people who want to lose weight do it in 90 days. Especially all Brides do before the wedding!

There are a number of packages to choose from for every budget, starting at about $50 a month. 

There are other benefits to the program such as the  three for free  incentive which allows users to get their product for free if they get three other people to join.

Description: Cosmetic Surgery Office & MedSpa Services Before establishing the Plastic Surgeons Institute in Mountain View and Carmel, California, Dr. Joshua Korman received his Bachelor’s Degree (with distinction in all subjects) and Medical Degree from Cornell University where he graduated at the top of his class (Alpha Omega Alpha). He completed his plastic surgery residency at Stanford University and furthered his education and experience with fellowships at Canniesburn Hospital in Glasgow, Scotland, and a Cosmetic Surgery Fellowship in Miami, Florida. He has taught at Stanford University for 20 years and is currently Adjunct Clinical Associate Professor. With a desire to give back to the community, Dr. Korman began the Clean Slate program in San Jose, California that gives former gang members the opportunity to rebuild their lives by removing tattoos that represent their past. Dr. Korman also volunteers his time with Breast Cancer Connections in Palo Alto, to educate breast cancer patients on their options for breast recon struction. He also has extensive experience working as a plastic and reconstructive surgeon in developing countries. Dr. Korman has appeared on many national television programs and newspapers as an expert in plastic surgery, including ABC’s “20/20” , CNN,The New York Times, Ebony Magazine and others. He continues to be on many “Best of”, “Top Doc” and “Readers Choice” publications.

Comments:
Hi, my company runs a unique photo booth. Our booth is an 8ftx8ftx8ft inflatable booth that has LED\'s in it. 
We have trendy props, a high-quality camera (Canon 5D mk3), custom playlist of music with the hottest songs right now, and touchscreen monitor.
This video shows what it\'s like inside our booth: https://youtu.be/hJ4cQdWx-70

Not only are we a unique booth, we would be a unique exhibitor as well.
I would love to talk to you about this over the phone, but basically, I would like to offer our booth to be at your fairs free of cost to anyone.
We will have custom photostrips that promote the Bay Area Wedding Fairs. They will have whatever background you want, with whatever text you guys want as well.
Our photobooth improves everyone\'s overall experience at the fairs. Not only will you have more happy brides, but vendors can participate in the booth as well.
All the while, people are taking home that photostrip that has your branded content. It\'s like slipping your business card into everyone\'s pockets.

We are a start-up, so we can\'t pay for a spot as an exhibitor, but I do think there\'s some real value of having us there. There\'s no money spent by having us there, and we do liven up the fair experience. On our side, we would be networking with those who enter the booth, and may have a contact sheet if people would like to book us. 

Please let me know what you think. Here\'s our site: http://www.level2p.com/l2partybooth.html

Thank you for your time,

Jared Lee

jared@level2p.com
